cs.MA, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper deals with modelling and analyzing complex mobile systems, which can be seen as a type of multi-agent system. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as mobility is often studied in the context of wireless networks and mobile computing. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as mobility patterns can be used to study social networks and information diffusion. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper uses discrete mathematics to model mobility. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with vehicular-mobile systems and traffic control.
